<P>
   RUSSIA-ASSESS (Moscow) _ News analysis: Judging by how the grand
and improbable alliance between Russia's westernized leadership and
its Communist critics exploded _ on television, spectacularly, in a
crossfire of accusations and threats _ one might think these people
hadn't a clue about what to do with their country. One would almost
be right. By Michael Wines.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-FLOOD (Xinzhen, China) _ On the plight of flood victims in
north China. In this far-north region known for early winters of
thick ice and bitter cold, the flood waters that now cover
thousands of villages will not recede for more than a month. So
huge numbers of refugees will face the winter's daily subzero
temperatures without a permanent home. By Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
