<P>
   EPA-TESTING (Union Dale, N.Y.) _ The Environmental Protection
Agency is gearing up for the most ambitious and methodical regime
ever proposed to test chemicals for harmful side effects. By John
H. Cushman Jr.
</P>
<P>
   NORTHWEST-DAKOTA (Grand Forks, N.D.) _ Almost everything in
Grand Forks, North Dakota's third-largest city, depends in some way
on Northwest Airlines. Northwest delivers the mail here. It brings
medical supplies for the hospital, flowers for the florists, even
goldfish for the pet stores. No other passenger airline flies in or
out. For the rest of this spread-out, wide-open state, this single
airline has become an umbilical cord. By Pam Belluck.
</P>
<P>
   ELDERHOSTEL (Kotzbebue, Alaska) _ Martha Rowe, three weeks shy
of her 77th birthday, found herself heading out of Kotzebue on a
beat-up yellow bus with a taped-together steering wheel, cracked
windshield and seats that slid around with every bump and curve in
the unpaved road. Her destination was a primitive fish camp on a
narrow strip of gravel beach between the tundra and the Chukchi
Sea, on the outskirts of Kotzebue, 26 miles above the Arctic
Circle, closer to Russia than Anchorage. ``I wanted an adventure,''
said Ms. Rowe, a retired clinical director of physical therapy at
the University of Florida in Gainesville. So did her fellow
travelers, 13 older men and women on a week-long odyssey with
Elderhostel, the nonprofit organization whose educational trips
here and abroad have become a rite of passage for a certain segment
of the 55 and over set. By Sara Rimer.
</P>
<P>
   ROWDY-RIVER-RIDERS (New Braunfels) _ In an effort to crack down
on drunkenness, nudity, littering, foul language and general
rowdiness from the thousands of people who float down the Guadalupe
River on inner tubes, extra cops and security people will be placed
along the river for the Labor Day weekend.
</P>
<P>
   HURRICANE-EROSION (North Topsail Beach, N.C.) _ In the aftermath
of Hurricane Bonnie, officials looking across the flat stretches of
beach that once held sand dunes can see they may be fighting a
losing battle against erosion. Hurricane Bonnie, which pummeled the
North Carolina coastline last week, took with it about 60 percent
of the dune line along North Topsail Beach, the northernmost
stretch of Topsail Island north of Wilmington.
</P>
