<P>
   BBN-MCGWIRE-DRUGS (Undated) _ Mark McGwire, the brawny St. Louis
Cardinals first baseman, has become a folk hero to many people for
his skill at baseball's most dramatic and clear-cut feat _ hitting
home runs. The ball either flies out of the park, or it doesn't.
There's no maybe. But McGwire's recent admission he has used a
testosterone-boosting compound for the last year has now led him
and his fans into a place where uncertainties and maybes abound. By
Kirk Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-SAMPRAS (Undated) _ If he could, Pete Sampras would work
undercover: punch in unnoticed, punch out with Grand Slam titles at
a clip his contemporaries can't come close to matching. But like it
or not, this year is different; this year, the cosmopolitan, and
cosmic, side he never knew he had has been showing up everywhere.
By Robin Finn.
