   &UR; FLORA AND FAUNA &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - Creepy crawlies: In England on a book tour, horror author
 &UR; Stephen King  &LR; told the Guardian he is ``terrified of spiders.
Snakes don't bother me. But I hate bugs.'' And at a Safeway in
Marin County,  &UR; Laura Merlo &LR;  couldn't figure out why Venus fly traps
and carnivorous plants are marked down with a sign that says,
``Great for Back to School.''
</P>
<P>
   - If you're in the need for an expert in ``the physiology of sex
steroids in the female African spotted hyena,'' look no further.
That's one of the fields of expertise of  &UR; Paul Licht &LR; , UC
Berkeley's new dean of biological sciences, says the Daily Cal.
</P>
