   - At a recent meeting of the European Parliament, members of the
Green Party proposed that the World Meteorological Institute name
storms and hurricanes after members of the Global Climate
Coalition, companies (Exxon, General Motors and Ford among them)
who deny that carbon emissions are contributing to climactic
changes. The new names, said the Green Party, would change
newspaper headlines to read, for instance: ``Exxon Kills 20 in
Miami.'' The measure was rejected by the parliament.
</P>
