<HEADLINE>
NCAA SHOULD TAKE HEAT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum heat was sooooo
nasty Sunday afternoon that...
</P>
<P>
   (Cough... gasp...)
</P>
<P>
   They posted a sign outside telling fans not to bring in
alcoholic beverages, glass bottles or cups, balls, Frisbees, boom
boxes, coolers, picnic baskets, fireworks, inflatables,
noisemakers, chairs, strollers or video cameras, but said nothing
about an IV....
</P>
<P>
   The Olympic torch atop the peristyle entrance suddenly became
lit in the third quarter _ probably by spontaneous combustion....
</P>
<P>
   If Purdue quarterback Drew Brees couldn't draw a breeze throwing
the ball 52 times, no one could....
</P>
<P>
   So here's an idea to the TV-money-hungry NCAAers who resist a
postseason playoff 'cause it would cut too much into the athletes'
academic pursuits but at the same time heartily endorse a special
early-season game before some players even know their summer-school
grades: It's not such a hot idea.
</P>
<P>
   Next time, you get to watch 91-year-old USC ``superfan'' Giles
Pellerin being carried out of the stadium at halftime in the middle
of his 786th consecutive game....
</P>
<P>
   Or if you're bent on making the kickoff at 11:30, shoot for
11:30 p.m....
</P>
<P>
   Merchandise update at the USC student store: Plenty of jerseys
with Nos. 10, 11, 24 and 55. Nuthin' with Carson Palmer's No. 15.
Yet...
</P>
<P>
   It's not meant as a rap on Mike Van Raaphorst, but Palmer should
be the starter by the Florida State game....
</P>
<P>
   Can anyone tell me the proper way to grip a golf club?...
Katzenmoyer?... Katzenmoyer?...
</P>
<P>
   If U.S. women's hockey star Cami Granato ends up as a color
analyst on the Kings' radio broadcasts _ making her the first
female to hold such a position _ you'll remember where you saw it
first....
</P>
<P>
   Ironic, isn't it, that Disney's new financial injection into the
NHL's TV budget will end up giving $4 million more to each of the
Ducks' opponents to sign players....
</P>
<P>
   Any dope can criticize Mark McAndro for his choice of dietary
supplements, but it's not as if the guy is dropping some illegal
amino acids....
</P>
<P>
   Marketing people in the know say Big Mac will be able to pull
down $500,000 to $1.5 million per endorsement deal if he snuffs out
Roger Maris' record. The freaks at GNC will be first in line....
</P>
<P>
   NL MVP voting: 1) Moises Alou, 2) Sammy Sosa, 3) Greg Maddux....
</P>
<P>
   Expected hot seller at this week's U.S. Open: An $11.95 wall
calendar featuring stars of the WTA Tour....
</P>
<P>
   Coming to a TV near you soon is NBC's master clubber Dick Enberg
doing an infomercial about a new beta-titanium driver for a golf
club company....
</P>
<P>
   Not enough golfers wear those Kangol wool berets like Samuel L.
Jackson, but they will soon....
</P>
<P>
   The LPGA is considering a senior tour of its own. 'Cept they'd
be called ``legend'' tournaments. Know any LPGA legends?...
</P>
<P>
   Put a gun to my head and ask who I think should win the MVP
honors this year in Major League Soccer, and I'd have to ask you to
just pull the trigger....
</P>
<P>
   For the record: Neither Major League Soccer, the WNBA, the ABL
nor the Arena Football League has lost one regular-season game
because of a labor dispute. And if they did, who'd notice?...
</P>
<P>
   Angels GM Bill Bavasi has pulled off better post-trade deals
this year than former Dodgers GM Fred Claire did last season when
he was trying to save his job....
</P>
<P>
   Tom Lasorda's new GM search should end after he finds out how
soon Bob Watson can move his stuff in....
</P>
<P>
   What's the proper phrase for that look Glenn Hoffman has in the
dugout every time the Fox camera is on him? Triple-A deer in the
headlights?...
</P>
<P>
   Memo to The Donald: Hire Kurt Rambis already....
</P>
<P>
   Cash-poor and locked-out Michael Jordan will run a four-day
adult basketball camp in Las Vegas in a few weeks. And the rules
are kinda strict: A) you gotta pay $15,000 to get in, B) you gotta
be at least 35 years of age, C) you gotta treat this thing
seriously _ it's no fantasy camp. If I'm paying $15,000, I think
there'd be no problem treating it seriously....
</P>
<P>
   Charlton Heston does commercials for lite beer. Lauren Bacall
does commercials for cat food. Why can't MJ do commercials for
bowling centers?
</P>
</TEXT>
